course.subject: MATH
course.name: Intermediate Complex Analysis
course.description: The objective is to familiarize students with concepts and techniques in Complex Analysis beyond an introductory course in Functions of a Complex Variable. This course covers a choice of topics in Complex Analysis in one complex variable such as complex potential theory, meromorphic functions, open Riemann surfaces, compact Riemann surfaces, normal families, geometric theory of holomorphic mappings and complex dynamics. Graded P or F.
